text: Rybnica () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Stara Kamienica, within Jelenia Góra County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south- western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately east of Stara Kamienica, west of Jelenia Góra, and west of the regional capital Wrocław. ==References== Category:Villages in Jelenia Góra County
title: Rybnica, Jelenia Góra County
